OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784074689
OL,3,C'Landmark' study to see blood test for
OL,4,CAlzheimer's offered by GPs
OL,6,FLed by Scottish Brain Sciences, the
OL,7,Fproject will explore how blood tests
OL,8,Fcould speed up diagnosis, help GPs
OL,9,Fdecide on the best care for patients,
OL,10,Fand give people earlier access to
OL,11,Fsupport and treatments.
OL,13,FThe aim is for up to 500 patients to
OL,14,Fbe referred for a test, making it the
OL,15,Flargest UK study of Alzheimer's blood
OL,16,Ftests in general practice.
OL,18,FAround 90,000 people in Scotland are
OL,19,Fliving with dementia, some 3,000 of
OL,20,Fwhom are younger than 65.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784074689
OL,3,C'Landmark' study to see blood test for
OL,4,CAlzheimer's offered by GPs
OL,6,FAn estimated two-thirds ` or 60,000 `
OL,7,Fhave Alzheimer's, which is a type of
OL,8,Fdementia that affects memory, thinking
OL,9,Fand behaviour.
OL,11,FThe project is supported by Roche
OL,12,FDiagnostics, which developed the blood
OL,13,Ftests being used in the research,
OL,14,Fknown as p-tau181 and p-tau217.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784074689
OL,3,C'Landmark' study to see blood test for
OL,4,CAlzheimer's offered by GPs
OL,6,FWhen found in the blood, these
OL,7,Fproteins reflect changes in the brain
OL,8,Fassociated with Alzheimer's, with
OL,9,Finternational research showing they
OL,10,Fmay detect or rule out the condition
OL,11,Fearlier and more accurately than many
OL,12,Fexisting memory tests or scans.
OL,14,FThe study aims to build GP experience
OL,15,Fand confidence in using the new tests,
OL,16,Fand to assess their value at the
OL,17,Fearliest stages of disease progression
OL,18,F` where quicker, more accurate
OL,19,Finformation could make the greatest
OL,20,Fdifference for patients and their
OL,21,Ffamilies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784074689
OL,3,C'Landmark' study to see blood test for
OL,4,CAlzheimer's offered by GPs
OL,6,FDr Sheelagh Harwell, senior associate
OL,7,FGP at GP-Plus in Edinburgh, is one of
OL,8,Fthe medics participating in the study.
OL,10,FShe said: "The BriDGe study heralds an
OL,11,Fexciting time in general practice as
OL,12,Fnew diagnostic blood tests become
OL,13,Favailable.
OL,15,F"Consultations are shifting from
OL,16,Fphysicians discussing dementia risk
OL,17,Fwith patients, to discussing brain
OL,18,Fhealth.
OL,26,@rD@KOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784074689
OL,3,C'Landmark' study to see blood test for
OL,4,CAlzheimer's offered by GPs
OL,6,F"An earlier diagnosis of Alzheimer's
OL,7,Fcan aid patients with lifestyle
OL,8,Fmodifications, allow them to access
OL,9,Fsupport sooner, and plan ahead."
OL,11,FA patient known as Martin, who has
OL,12,Ftaken part in a previous Scottish
OL,13,FBrain Sciences study, experienced
OL,14,Fsignificant changes to his thinking
OL,15,Fand memory, and said the current
OL,16,Fdiagnostics process is confusing.
OL,18,F"I have had conflicting information
OL,19,Ffrom healthcare professionals which
OL,20,Fhas left me in limbo," he said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@`O]zD@AOU|D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784074689
OL,3,C'Landmark' study to see blood test for
OL,4,CAlzheimer's offered by GPs
OL,6,F"I had tests through my GP and was
OL,7,Ftold it is likely I have Alzheimer's
OL,8,Fdisease so I was referred to a
OL,9,Fpsychiatrist at my local hospital.
OL,11,F"The psychiatrist told me I didn't
OL,12,Fhave Alzheimer's, without carrying out
OL,13,Fany tests. I was quite shocked.
OL,15,F"If a blood test was available through
OL,16,Fmy GP that could make the diagnosis
OL,17,Fprocess easier ` and potentially
OL,18,Fquicker ` I would be very willing to
OL,19,Ftake it."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUwD@AOU{D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784074689
OL,3,C'Landmark' study to see blood test for
OL,4,CAlzheimer's offered by GPs
OL,6,FProfessor Craig Ritchie, chief
OL,7,Finvestigator of the BriDGe project and
OL,8,Fchief executive and founder at
OL,9,FScottish Brain Sciences, described
OL,10,Fblood tests for Alzheimer's as "one of
OL,11,Fthe most exciting developments in
OL,12,Fdementia research in a generation".
OL,14,FHe continued: "We now need to
OL,15,Funderstand how they work in real-world
OL,16,Fhealthcare. By partnering with 50 GPs
OL,17,Fand up to 500 patients, BriDGe will
OL,18,Fshow how these tests could transform
OL,19,Fthe way we detect, diagnose and
OL,20,Fultimately treat Alzheimer's disease."
OL,26,@rD@`OUtD@bO]vD@OOU|D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784074689
OL,3,C'Landmark' study to see blood test for
OL,4,CAlzheimer's offered by GPs
OL,6,FAshton Harper, global medical affairs
OL,7,Flead for neurosciences at Roche
OL,8,FDiagnostics, said: "This landmark
OL,9,Fcollaboration between GPs, researchers
OL,10,Fand patients across Scotland has the
OL,11,Fpotential to transform the way
OL,12,FAlzheimer's disease is diagnosed.
OL,14,F"By paving the way for earlier
OL,15,Fdetection through primary care, it
OL,16,Fcould help more people access the
OL,17,Fright treatment, care and support at
OL,18,Fthe earliest possible stage."
OL,26,@pD@TOUvD@AOUzD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784074689
OL,3,C'Landmark' study to see blood test for
OL,4,CAlzheimer's offered by GPs
OL,6,FProfessor Tara Spires-Jones, professor
OL,7,Fof neurodegeneration at the University
OL,8,Fof Edinburgh, described the rollout of
OL,9,Fblood tests for use by GPs as
OL,10,F"excellent news".
OL,12,FShe added: "Elevated levels of the
OL,13,Fprotein pTau in blood indicate that
OL,14,Fpeople have Alzheimer's disease-
OL,15,Fassociated pathology in their brains.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@PO]tD@LOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784074689
OL,3,C'Landmark' study to see blood test for
OL,4,CAlzheimer's offered by GPs
OL,6,F"While not everyone with this
OL,7,Fpathology will go on to develop
OL,8,Fdementia, people with cognitive
OL,9,Fsymptoms and a positive blood test are
OL,10,Flikely in the early stages of
OL,11,FAlzheimer's disease, meaning this test
OL,12,Fwill help with diagnosis.
OL,14,F"This will be particularly important
OL,15,Fin the future as it is likely that new
OL,16,Ftreatments will become available that
OL,17,Fcan remove Alzheimer's pathology from
OL,18,Fthe brain and slow disease
OL,19,Fprogression."
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU{D@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
